‘Liverpool is not the ground that Manchester United has won a lot (at) so when we show it again in Liverpool then we are a little bit further, I believe.’

United have had Chris Smalling and Angel di Maria sent off in big games against Manchester City and Arsenal this season, and Van Gaal warned that they have to keep their cool at Anfield.

He hinted that he has deliberately been winding them up in training to test their temperaments.

‘I am the referee in the games that we have had on the training pitch and I have whistled in the way that they have to control their aggression, for example,’ he added.

 ‘To prepare them already the atmosphere. And I have mentioned that to them after lunch. Control of emotion is also a talent.’

